  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether esophageal dysmotility and dilatation is an
      important complication in the long term follow-up following laparoscopic gastric banding for
      morbid obesity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Using a yearly barium swallow the diameter of the esophagus will be monitored over the
      period.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
